-- Idemitsu to Develop 10-Megawatt Solar Plant in Western Japan
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2012-12-03T07:23:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-03/idemitsu-to-develop-10-megawatt-solar-plant-in-western-japan.html
Idemitsu Kosan Co. (5019) , a Japanese
refiner, will develop a 10-megawatt solar-power station in
western  Japan .  The plant, with capacity to supply about 3,800 homes, will
be built on the site of Idemitsu’s former refinery in Himeji
city, Hyogo prefecture, the Tokyo-based company said today in a
 statement . It’s scheduled to start operations in March 2014.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
 cwatanabe5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  